		<description><![CDATA[Call for Reviewers for The Self-Publisher's Ultimate Resource Guide]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a class="post_image_link" href="http://www.thebookdesigner.com/2015/01/call-for-reviewers/" title="Permanent link to Call for Reviewers"><img class="post_image aligncenter" src="http://www.thebookdesigner.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/bigstock-Male-Professor-Shouting-Though-64053307.jpg" width="530" height="275" alt="Post image for Call for Reviewers" /></a>
</p><p>Have you ever spent time researching online, going from site to site trying to find the kind of help you need? Sure, me too, everybody does. <em>That makes you a good candidate to review my new book.</em></p>
<p>And I think it&#8217;s one of the reasons <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Self-Publishers-Ultimate-Resource-Guide-Directory--ebook/dp/B00QSKUS2Q/?tag=marinbo-20" target="_blank">The Self-Publisher&#8217;s Ultimate Resource Guide</a> has been so popular. It really helps.</p>
<p>The book, coauthored with traditional publishing pro <a href="http://www.spresourceguide.com/" target="_blank">Betty Kelly Sargent</a>, was #1 in its category on Amazon.com on publication day, and has stayed there ever since, almost a month later.</p>
<p>That tells me people are finding real value. The over 850 curated, verified, and up-to-date listings to service providers of all kinds are saving people time and making resources easier to find.</p>
<p>When you have something that&#8217;s helping authors so much, you naturally want to share it with as many  people as you can.</p>
<p>That&#8217;s where you come in.</p>
<p>We&#8217;ve set aside a limited number of free review copies and I want to give them all away. I&#8217;ve often counseled authors that one of the best ways to build the buzz around their book is by giving away copies to people who will help promote the book.</p>
<p>So if you&#8217;d like to review the Resource Guide, I&#8217;d like to give you one of those free copies before they run out.</p>
<p>Just fill out the simple form below to get started:<br />
(If you&#8217;re having any difficulty with the form, you can also complete it here: <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1sarAPx52zblnxVk5tPM0scXUhmTzCcj6CkCW9XPV-e8/viewform?c=0&#038;w=1" target="_blank">SPURG Reviewer Request</a>.)</p>
<p>It only takes a minute.</p>
<p>And thanks for your help.</p>
<p><iframe src="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1sarAPx52zblnxVk5tPM0scXUhmTzCcj6CkCW9XPV-e8/viewform?embedded=true" width="530" height="1125" frameborder="0" marginheight="0" marginwidth="0">Loading&#8230;</iframe></p>
<p><font size = "-1"><em>This offer will expire at midnight Pacific on Friday, January 16, 2015.</em></font></p>
<h3>What People Are Saying</h3>
<p>Here are some early reviews of the <em>Resource Guide</em> from industry professionals:</p>
<p>&#8220;An essential reference to the best publishing resources for every self published author. Highly recommended!&#8221;<br />
&#8212;<strong>Mark Coker</strong>, Smashwords founder</p>
<p>&#8220;Most authors are excited about the promise of self-publishing&#8211;until they actually try to do it. Then they quickly realize they will need a team of professionals to prepare, publish, and promote their book. And that&#8217;s where they get stuck. They don&#8217;t have the connections. That&#8217;s where <em>The Self-Publisher&#8217;s Ultimate Resource Guide</em> is a life-saver. This is the missing link that will enable authors to capitalize on the self-publishing revolution and become captains of their own literary destiny. I highly recommend it.&#8221;<br />
&#8212;<strong>Michael Hyatt</strong>, New York Times Bestselling Author and Former CEO, Thomas Nelson Publishers</p>
<p>&#8220;Independent authors need a team to help create a fantastic finished product, and finding the right people can be a challenge when you first start out. This book will help authors to locate professionals to edit, publish and market their work&#8211;helping them to stand out in the crowded marketplace.&#8221;<br />
&#8212;<strong>Joanna Penn</strong>, The Creative Penn<br />
