<strong><font color="crimson">JF:</font> </strong>I could just repeat the comment from your other cover above. Authors might consider working <em>with</em> a designer until they learn more about how to use type.</p>
<hr />
<p><font color="darkred">Bonnie Ferrante</font> submitted <strong>Terror at White Otter Castle</strong> designed by Bonnie Ferrante. &#8220;A campy suspense in the tone of 1950s horror comics.&#8221;<br />
