<strong><font color="crimson">JF:</font> </strong>But what does it all mean? And why do we have a font right out of the Renaissance along with Comic Sans (or one of it&#8217;s imitators)?</p>
<hr />
<p><font color="darkred">Grayer Vaughan</font> submitted <strong>The Silent Violent Few</strong> designed by Grayer Vaughan. &#8220;The cover design was inspired by the submissive pose that a character, Frankie aka Dandelion, does in the book. This is a pivotal scene that was able to be captured and placed on the book cover to represent the tone of the book. The rope corset is a reflection of the struggle she experiences.&#8221;<br />
